content: Terrible app. Doesn't help with learning, rather I end up guessing until I get everything right because it doesn't tell you why you got a wrong answer, which wastes an hour of my time. Additionally, I get wrong answer because my fingers are too big to select the ones I want. Terrible app and DOES NOT deseve $1.
No updates in years, a warning that it may not work at startup, and it seems like it doesn't accept correct multiple choice answers.
Not an effective way of learning
THE ANSWERS CHANGE AND IT SUCKS
It's a waste of $1. This app is required for my physics class, but the app doesn't even work because its not compatible with the latest version on Android.
It sucks! This is the only app I have ever gotten that made me want to throw my phone!
This app is terrible! It does not even explain to you why you got the question incorrect. It needs some improvements.
I have to do the mops for my so physics class tommorow so I spent a dollar to get this app. But it won't even let me start.

Riddled with bugs and poor programming. The help screen has other windows pop up, blocking the information needed, the app doesn't go into full screen, and selecting options does nothing half of the time.
It made me to love physics
My teacher requires us to do these as a grade and I can't get the keyboard to open for the questions that require the answer to be typed out.

I had trouble selecting answer choices - the keyboard didn't open reliably, the touch screen didn't map reliably, and it was difficult to erase errantly selected answers. Until these difficulties are fixed, the app is impossible to use.
This thing sucks as an app waste of a dollar
Gets to the heart of physics.
